  - var articleTitle = "Menubars: Complex"

block section

  p In Codebase, responsive menubars have further been developed into complex navigation systems capable of handling multiple menus/menubars, dropdowns and inline forms (similar to the Bootstrap navbar and Foundation top bar). They are complex inasmuch as they can handle all these optional elements &ndash; but their HTML is still quite simple.

  p The complex menu/menubar introduces some optional nested elements: brand, #[a(href="#components-activator") activator] control (for the navicon) and activator content. Also, since in a complex menubar the actual menubar(s) are nested elements, their equivalent alignment classes are named using double underscores (following #[a(href="http://getbem.com/introduction/") BEM]).

