  h3 Incorporating Dropdown Menus
  
  p When a dropdown is incorporated into a menubar, the first click on a parent link activates the drodown to reveal the child menu items (without the parent link being followed).

  p Clicking the parent link #[i again] (i.e. while the dropdown content is activated) will follow the parent link to its linked page.

  p Clicking anywhere else outside the activated dropdown content will dismiss the dropdown. (Clicking another dropdown will deactivate the active dropdown and activate the newly clicked dropdown instead.)

  p #[b Note:] you won't have to use the responsive dropdown modifier classes (e.g. #[code .dropdown--md-up]) because the responsive menubar modifier class (e.g. #[code .menu--menubar-md]) incorporates dropdown mixins above the breakpoint width. Also, the caret that is built into dropdowns will be hidden (because not relevant) below the menubar media query breakpoint width.
  
